# Comments: No Full Stops, New Line Per Sentence

- **No full stops**: Do not use periods (`.`) in comments.
- **One sentence per line**: Start each new sentence or clause on its own line.

This applies to inline comments (`# ...`) and block comments.

## Examples

```python
# ❌ BAD — full stops and multiple sentences on one line
# Fetch the user. Return None if not found.

# ✅ GOOD — no full stops, new sentence on new line
# fetch the user
# return None if not found
```
